{
  "texts": [
    "As we explore these interconnected themes, the relationships between smell and taste, supported by advanced AI techniques, emerge as critical areas for advancing our understanding and enhancing practical applications.",
    "Despite significant progress, several critical limitations continue to impede the effective integration of AI into olfactory and gustatory research.",
    "First, existing datasets frequently exhibit substantial limitations, including small sizes, class imbalance, and insufficient representation of diverse populations.",
    "These constraints reduce the robustness and generalizability of AI-driven sensory models, leading to biases that disproportionately reflect Western dietary habits and sensory experiences (Daneshjou et al. 2021).",
    "Expanding and diversifying these datasets is essential for developing universally reliable and culturally sensitive AI tools."
  ]
}